<FIRST>u w AM-MarsObit     06-01 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mars Obit,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Audrey Mars Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Audrey Meyer Mars, long-time volunteer for the
American Cancer Society, died of cancer at her Washington home
Thursday. She was 79.
   Mrs. Mars, wife of Forrest Edward Mars Sr., retired head of the
privately owned Mars candy concern, served as a vice president of
the society and helped establish cancer programs in several
countries during more than 30 years of anti-cancer work. Government
and private bodies in the Philippines, Thailand and Poland gave her
awards.
   From 1965 to 1975, she was a director of the candy company. She
served on the boards of several other charitable and medical
organizations.
   She is survived by her husband, who lives in Las Vegas, Nev.,
three children, 10 grandchildren and two great-grandchildren.
</TEXT>
