<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     06-01 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>AP Names News Editor for West Virginia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W. Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   John A. Raby Jr., night supervisor in
the Detroit bureau of The Associated Press, has been named news
editor in the Charleston, W.Va., bureau.
   The appointment was announced Wednesday by Charleston Chief of
Bureau Terry Kinney.
   Raby, 27, a native of Dearborn, Mich., graduated from Michigan
State University in 1984 with a bachelor's degree in journalism.
   He worked as a vacation relief staff member in the Detroit
bureau prior to graduation, joined AP there in 1984, and for the
past two years has been night supervisor.
</TEXT>
