<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--SeamanDefects     06-01 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Seaman Defects,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviet Seaman Reportedly Jumps Ship to Defect</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANAKKALE, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet seaman was missing after
reportedly jumping into the Dardanalles strait while attempting to
defect to Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia news agency said.
   The agency identified the missing seaman as engineer Tetkhiladze
Archil, who was aboard the Soviet freighter Nikolai Kuznetsov. It
quoted the ship's captain as saying Archil jumped into the strait
before dawn Wednesday.
   The Soviet vessel, en route from Spain to a Soviet Black Sea
port, searched unsuccessfully for the seaman before continuing its
voyage, the agency said.
   Anatolia quoted unidentified local officials as saying it would
be very difficult for the seaman to survive and swim to shore
because of the strong currents in the strait, which is up to 6
miles wide at some places.
</TEXT>
