<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--BatmobileLogo     06-01 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Batmobile Logo,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Batman Dropped By Cops</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have agreed to drop the Batman
logo from the Breath Alcohol Testing's ``batmobile.''
   Warner Communications Inc., which owns the DC Comics series on
which the Batman television character is based, asked the
department earlier this year to remove the logo.
   It said the logo's use constituted trademark and copyright
infringement.
   ``I promised that we would take the emblem off if they wanted us
to. It's not going to reduce the number of DWI arrests we get,''
Police Chief Ron Axtell said.``We don't have time to fight it in
court. We have too many things to do.''
   Warner learned of the logo and local batmobile after seeing them
featured in a newspaper article.
</TEXT>
