<FIRST>r a PM-Nielsens     06-01 0344</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Nielsens,0354</SECOND>
<HEAD>NBC Scores Another Top 10 Sweep</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC has become so dominant in prime time, it's
mostly busy these days breaking its own records in increasingly
rapid fashion.
   Last week, NBC had the top 10 shows in the A.C. Nielsen Co.
ratings, landing both parts of the critically acclaimed two-part
movie ``I Know My First Name is Steven'' in the top two spots.
   The last time a network swept the top 10 was three weeks ago,
when NBC had the top 11 shows.
   This time, CBS broke into the list at 11th with its Sunday
movie, ``Kojak: The Price of Justice.''
   NBC won the week, a record 49th in a row, with a 14.1 rating to
CBS' 10.1 and ABC's 9.1.
   ``I Know My First Name Is Steven,'' the fact-based story of
teen-ager who returned to his family after seven years in the
captivity of the pedophile who kidnapped him, had a two-part
average rating of 24.5 and a 39 share and was the highest-rated
multi-part movie of the 1988-89 season, second only to CBS'
four-part ``Lonesome Dove.''
   The rest of the top 10 were ``Cheers,'' ``The Cosby Show,'' ``A
Different World,'' ``Golden Girls,'' ``Dear John,'' ``Empty Nest,''
``Hunter'' and ``L.A. Law.''
   The NBC movie and ``60 Minutes'' were the only non-repeat
programs among the top 20 last week.
   The ``CBS Evening News'' led the news ratings, when student
protests in China continued to be the big story. CBS had an average
rating of 9.2 and a 21 share, ``ABC World News Tonight'' had an 8.8
and 19 share, and ``NBC Nightly News'' had an 8.4 and 19.
   Each rating point equals 904,000 households with television. The
share is a percentage of sets in use.
   The lowest-rated shows of the week were: ``Mission Impossible,''
``Family Ties Special,'' ``West 57th,'' ``Paradise,'' ``North &amp;
South, Book Two, Part Three,'' ``Earth Star Voyager, Part One,''
``Family Ties,'' ``Incredible Sunday,'' ``Lots of Luck _ Magical
World of Disney'' and ``Beyond the Cold War: Risk and Opportunity.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
