<HEAD>Jean Harris Remorseful Over Tarnower's Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jean Harris, killer of ``Scarsdale Diet Doctor''
Herman Tarnower, says she is remorseful about his death.
   ``Remorse has become an appendage to me,'' Ms. Harris told
Independent Network News in an interview this week at the Bedford
Hills Correctional Facility in Westchester County.
   ``It's like another skin and I live in it and I always will,''
said Ms. Harris, 66.
   She said she feels ``terrible, terribly sorry. You don't throw
it off.''
   Ms. Harris said Tarnower could have prevented his death by
talking to her calmly when she confronted him about a love affair.
Instead, she said, he called her ``crazy'' and hit her in the face.
She then shot him to death.
   Ms. Harris was sentenced to 15 years to life in prison in March
1981. She has appealed twice to Gov. Mario Cuomo for clemency,
without success.
   The interview is scheduled to be broadcast tonight.
