<HEAD>Two Police Copters Crash Over Famous Park In Rome</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two police helicopters collided during exercises
over the Villa Borghese gardens today and one exploded, killing two
policemen and injuring two, authorities said.
   No civilians in the park were injured, said Maricello Primavera,
a spokesman for the carabinieri police force.
   The helicopters were practicing for an annual June 7 celebration
of Italy's paramilitary police, he said. The cause of the accident
was not known.
   The two officers killed were aboard the helicopter that
exploded, he said.
   The remains of the aircraft crashed onto Piazza Siena, a square
in the 1,700-acre park on the edge of historic Rome. The gardens
are a favorite spot for Romans and tourists.
