<HEAD>With PM-Wright</HEAD>
<HEAD>Jim Wright III Attacks Gingrich As `Another Joe McCarthy'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   House Speaker Jim Wright's son today called
Rep. Newt Gingrich, who started the investigation of his father,
``another Joe McCarthy'' and said the speaker was the victim of the
``reactionary right.''
   Jim Wright III, interviewed from Santa Fe, N.M., on NBC-TV's
``Today'' show, at first said he would not name anyone in his
criticism of a House investigation that led to his father's
announcement Wednesday to resign.
   But, later in the interview, he referred to House Minority Whip
Gingrich, R-Ga., who initiated the investigation of Wright before
he joined the GOP House leadership.
   ``I think the Republicans are going to realize that he's just a
loose cannon on the deck, another Joe McCarthy,'' said Wright, 44,
who is a personnel administrator with the State of New Mexico. He
said he agreed with his father, however, that ``mindless
cannibalism'' should end and Democrats should not go after Gingrich.
   ``As soon as he becomes an embarrassment to them (Republicans),
they'll back away from him and let him sink on his own,'' the
younger Wright said.
   The speaker's son said he was giving his opinion, not his
father's, when he compared Gingrich with the late Sen. Joseph
McCarthy, who led efforts to expose people McCarthy labled as
communists in government and private industry.
   ``I feel that the reactionary right has pulled a page out of Joe
McCarthy's book, to use a tactic against my father called the big
lie; tell a lie about somebody over and over long enough and not
let him defned himself and you're bound to get him,'' said Wright.
   ``I think he's been black-listed for being an effective opponent
of the reactionary right,'' he said.
