<HEAD>Soviet Union Launches 3 Satellites</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union has launched three Cosmos
satellites into orbit, the Tass news agency said Thursday.
   The satellites were lifted into orbit Wednesday on a single
Proton rocket.
   Cosmos-2022 and Cosmos-2023 will be used test the equipment of
the space navigation system Glonass, which determines the bearings
of civil aircraft and marine and fishing fleets, the official news
agency said.
   Cosmos-2024 will be used to forecast the movement of spacecraft
and for geophysical research.
