<HEAD>Demonstrators March in NYC Against Salvador Policy</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Salvador, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 120 demonstrators marched and chanted
against U.S. policy in El Salvador on Thursday and nearly half were
arrested for stopping traffic or blocking a building where Sen.
Daniel P. Moynihan has an office.
   The protesters gathered at the Salvadoran consulate in Manhattan
and spattered its wall with red paint. They marched to Moynihan's
New York City office, but he was in Washington and the protesters
were not admitted to the building.
