blocking the building entrance and 37 for halting traffic.
   The demonstration was sponsored by the New York Coalition to
Stop the U.S. War in El Salvador, which said it targeted Moynihan,
a Democrat, because ``he has the power to make a difference, but
instead he supports the murderous status quo.''
