<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--FatalFumes     06-01 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Fatal Fumes,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Overcome By Fumes, Die In Sewer Sump</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. AUGUSTINE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two construction company workers were
overcome by gases while working on a sewer project, and both died,
police said. One died trying to rescue the other.
   The men were removing debris from one of the city's new sewer
pumps in an 18-foot-deep sump Wednesday afternoon, said Public
Works Director Jack Cubbedge.
   When one man was overcome and passed out, the other tried to
flag down motorists before climbing into the well to rescue his
co-worker, said Sgt. Steve Fricke.
   When a fire-rescue team arrived, neither man was breathing.
   Cubbedge said the men worked for Satilla Industrial Contractors
of Waycross, Ga., a subcontractor on the sewer project. They were
identified as Percy Cummings, 28, of Lake City, and Ronny Clifford
Odom, 40, of Metter, Ga.
</TEXT>
