<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SAfrica-Stoning     06-01 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--SAfrica-Stoning,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Whites Sentenced to 10 Years For Stoning Death of Black</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two whites each were sentenced
to 10 years in prison Thursday for killing an 8-year-old black who
was struck in the head by a stone thrown from the back of a pickup
truck.
   According to testimony, the two were part of a group of high
school students who skipped classes Oct. 12, 1987, and went
drinking at a park. On the drive back, they decided to throw stones
at pedestrians.
   Shane Mitchell, 18, was convicted of murder for throwing the
stone that killed Ronnie Pitso. The youth died of brain injuries.
   Timothy Beddingfield, 20, also was convicted of murder on the
grounds that the knew the stone was about to be thrown and did
nothing to stop Mitchell.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
