<FIRST>r a AM-BeachRape     06-01 0316</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Beach Rape,0324</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Charged, Others Sought in Gang Rape at Beach</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police have made one arrest and
are seeking other participants and about 10 bystanders in a gang
rape at the beach of this Florida Panhandle resort town,
authorities said Thursday.
   A 17-year-old vacationer from Tennessee returned Tuesday to the
beach where she reported being raped a day earlier and identified
one of four attackers, Police Chief Lee Sullivan said.
   Gregory Shane Hardin, 18, of Boaz, Ala., was arrested on a
sexual battery charge, Sullivan said. Hardin was in jail Thursday
under $50,000 bond on the felony, which is Florida's equivalent of
a rape charge.
   The chief called the attack the most pitiful sexual crime he has
seen during his years of law enforcement.
   ``It should never have happened,'' he said. ``It's not going to
happen again. We made some patrol procedure changes and moved some
of our resources to the beach.''
   Sullivan said rape is rare in the community, but a gang rape in
front of witnesses is a ``sad commentary on us all.''
   Hardin and possibly one other man allegedly raped the teen-ager
while two others helped hold her down, Sullivan said. The victim
was bruised on her ankles, wrists, breasts and genitals.
   ``The lab is going to be able to tell us how many assaults we
had,'' he said.
   The young woman was vacationing with her mother and a friend to
celebrate her high school graduation. While her friend left for
something to eat, she joined an impromptu party near the beachfront
Holiday Inn, where she met Hardin and another man, said police Lt.
Howard Parks.
   At about 2 a.m., each man allegedly took her by an arm and
forced her to go with them to a nearby sailboat rental business.
She was raped on one of the boats while the bystanders watched,
Parks said.
</TEXT>
