<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BATTLE CREEK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gregory Quinn and fiancee Corlinda
Reedy had planned a garden wedding in September, but they've moved
it up _ in more ways than one.
   They now plan to wed on June 24 and celebrate by taking their
first ride in a hot-air balloon. The ceremony comes on the final
day of the Battle Creek International Balloon Championship.
   Between 50 and 100 people have been invited to the ceremony in
the pilot briefing hangar. Quinn and Reedy will take to the skies
following a champagne toast and dance.
   ``It's going to be a gas _ propane, to be exact,'' said Quinn,
30, sales manager at a local camera shop. ``It just happened to
fall on the balloon championship and I proposed the wedding there.
(Her) first reaction was horror. She's excited, but totally
horrified.''
   The first wedding held during the balloon champioship was in
1985, executive director Barbara Brenner said.
