<FIRST>a d BC-FUN--Food-Salad adv31   06-01 0229</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-FUN--Food-Salad, adv 31,0237</SECOND>
<HEAD>$adv 31 FOOD 5-26</HEAD>
<HEAD>For AMS of Wednesday, May 31, and PMs and AMs thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>HEAD: Stay cool with crisp spinach salad</HEAD>
<BYLINE>ART: 2 col salad on a plate    ___ ^By NANCY BYAL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Better Homes and Gardens Magazine</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Food Editor</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Popeye, the spinach-craving strongman sailor of the comic page,
would love this side-dish salad because it's full of his favorite
food. It's easy on the cook in the galley, too, with just three
ingredients plus the zippy dressing.
   COTTAGE CHEESE AND SPINACH SALAD
   7 cups torn fresh spinach (10 ounces)
   1{ cups cream-style cottage cheese
   { cup chopped walnuts
   Creamy Dressing or bottled creamy dressing
   Place spinach in a large salad bowl. Spoon cottage cheese on top
of spinach in a ring. Sprinkle with walnuts. Pour on dressing; toss
lightly until spinach is coated. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
   Creamy Dressing: In a small mixing bowl stir together { cup
dairy sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 tablespoon prepared
horseradish, { teaspoon dry mustard and \ teaspoon salt. Using a
wire whisk, gradually blend in 3 tablespoons herb-flavored vinegar.
Cover and chill until serving time.
   Nutrition information per serving: 194 cal., 11 g pro., 11 g
carb., 13 g fat, 17 mg chol., 368 mg sodium. U.S. RDA: 69 percent
vit. A, 23 percent vit. C, 13 percent riboflavin, 12 percent
calcium.
</TEXT>
