<HEAD>STYLE 5-26</HEAD>
<HEAD>HEAD: Prepare your house for vacation, too</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARROLLTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When you go on vacation, make sure your
house is well protected.
   Even if you have a monitored electronic security system, have a
neighbor collect newspapers and mail. Put outdoor lights and at
least one indoor light on automatic timers. Let your friends know
when you are leaving and when you will return. Consider hiring a
house-sitter for extended absences.
   Peter A. Michel of Brink's Home Security Inc. offers these other
suggestions for year-round protection:
   Join a crime-watch program in your neighborhood.
   Leave your outside lights on at night. If your neighborhood is
dimly lit, lobby for better community lighting or install flood
lights on your home.
   Keep hedges nextrimmed to no higher than the
window sill to make burglars more visible.
   When you leave the house, leave tt to your house he stereo or television
on. The
noise will ward off most would-be intruders.
</TEXT>
