<FIRST>r f BC-Revlon-Nancy     06-01 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Revlon-Nancy,0176</SECOND>
<HEAD>Revlon Elects Nancy Reagan to Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former First Lady Nancy Reagan has been elected
to the board of Revlon Group Inc., the company announced Thursday.
   Revlon Chairman Ronald Perelman said in a statement that Mrs.
Reagan had gained insight during her husband's tenure as president
and displayed leadership in fighting drug abuse that ``will add an
important additional perspective to the Revlon board of directors.''
   Mrs. Reagan, who now resides in California and is completing a
book about her life, will serve as a director for an indefinite
term. Revlon spokesman Jim Conroy would not comment on how much she
will be paid to serve on the 15-member board.
   He said Mrs. Reagan was notified by telephone after she was
approved by directors at a regular meeting on Wednesday. She
replaces Jewel Lafontant, a Chicago attorney who resigned to serve
as an ambassador-at-large for the State Department.
   The privately-held Revlon's business units include the cosmetic
manufacturer Revlon Inc. and National Health Laboratories.
</TEXT>
