<SECOND>BC-British Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,f0034,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed lower Thursday on the London
Stock Exchange, as caution prevailed despite a slight easing of
recent worries about the outlook for British interest rates.
   Contributing to the more relaxed attitude were a recovery by the
pound and a decision by the West German central bank not to raise
its key interest rates.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 11
points, or 0.5 percent, to close at 2,103.4.
   The Financial Times 30-share index finished 10.1 points lower at
1,745.6. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 7.11 points to
close at 1,202.43.
   Volume slowed to 512.5 million shares from Wednesday's 536.3
million shares.
</TEXT>
