<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-BritishTelecom     06-01 0214</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-British Telecom,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>British Telecom Earnings Rise 2.3 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British Telecom Ltd. said Thursday its earnings
rose 2.3 percent in its fourth fiscal quarter when measured
according to American accounting standards.
   The company said it expected a year of progress in spite of
``the less buoyant outlook for the domestic economy.''
   Quarterly earnings rose to 358 million British pounds, or $605
million at current exchange rates, from 350 million pounds a year
earlier. The fourth quarter of the year-earlier period had two
extra working days.
   Earnings per American depository receipt rose to 59 pence, or
$1, from 58 pence a year earlier. Each ADR represents 10 shares of
British Telecom ordinary stock.
   Revenue rose 7.4 percent to 2.89 billion pounds, or $4.85
billion, in the three-month period ended March 31 from 2.69 billion
pounds a year earlier.
   For the year as a whole, British Telecom said its earnings rose
to 1.52 billion pounds, or $2.57 billion, from 1.39 billion pounds
a year earlier.
   Earnings per ADR rose to 2.52 pounds, or $4.26, from 2.31 pounds.
   Revenue rose to 11.1 billion pounds, or $18.7 billion, from 10.2
billion pounds a year earlier.
   British Telecom reports results differently to American
stockholders and British stockholders to reflect differences in
national accounting standards.
</TEXT>
