<HEAD>Investment Group Discloses Stake in America West</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An investment group that includes Martin T.
Sossnoff and Nelson Peltz disclosed Thursday it holds an 8.46
percent interest in America West Airlines.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the
group said Atalanta-Sossnoff Capital Corp. holds 16,400 common
shares plus $16.6 million in 11{ percent convertible debentures,
nearly the equivalent of 1.5 million common shares. The investment
group said it paid $17.75 million for its holdings in America West,
an aggressive regional carrier.
   The group also told the SEC the interest was acquired solely for
investment.
   America West recently made a $415 million offer for strikebound
Eastern Airlines' Northeast shuttle, challenging Eastern's earlier
agreement to sell the lucrative service to developer Donald Trump
for $365 million. Last Thursday, U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Burton R.
Lifland approved the sale to Trump, after America West failed to
secure financing for its offer by a Wednesday deadline set by
Eastern.
   The principal owner of Atalanta-Sosnoff Capital, an investment
management and brokerage business, is Sossnoff, who also is
chairman. Peltz, another major investor, is on the group's board of
directors.
   The America West debenture offering became available Jan. 1 in
exchange for earlier 7{ percent and 7\ percent issues and allowed
the airline to retire some long-term debt.
