<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
195,072 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
234,270, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production also is lower than the same week a year
ago, in which 202,094 cars and light trucks were produced, the
trade journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 122,695 cars this week,
compared with 148,363 a week ago and 138,745 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 72,377,
compared with last week's 85,907 and last year's 72,349.
   Canadian automakers were to build 22,390 cars this week, down
from 23,838 a week ago and down from last year's 26,559.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,637,
compared with 21,348 a week ago and 20,202 in the same week last
year.
